# Every merge to codex-platform main requires explicit approval from a code
# owner. Combined with branch protection's `require_code_owner_reviews: true`
# and `required_approving_review_count: 1`, this means: no PR (including the
# maintainer's own — admin can still bypass for solo work) reaches main
# without a deliberate approval click.
#
# Rationale: codex-platform's `sync-v1` propagates to consumer repos that
# track it. A merged-but-malicious commit here can flow into those
# consumers' CI with org-write tokens. Requiring an explicit per-PR
# approval is the cheapest defense against subtle skill / sync-engine
# weaponization until the structural mitigations (sandboxed engine,
# consumer-side destination allowlist) land.
#
# CODEOWNERS syntax: https://docs.github.com/repositories/managing-your-repositories-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

